title: Concerts announced this week
text:
Concert Update | New Shows & Music News Concerts announced this week Selena Gomez will perform at the Marcus Amphitheater on June 29 during Summerfest. Oct. 8, 2015 11:33 a.m. Getty Images Thomas Rhett will play at the Rave on Dec. 12. 
Selena Gomez: June 29, Marcus Amphitheater, Summerfest, 200 N. Harbor Dr. Showtime and prices to be announced. Tickets on sale 10 a.m. Saturday, Oct. 17 at the box office, (800) 745-3000 and ticketmaster.com. Tickets include general Summerfest admission. 
Big Snow Show X featuring Weezer, Of Monsters and Men and Panic! at the Disco: 7:30 p.m. Dec. 10 to 12, Eagles Ballroom, the Rave, 2401 W. Wisconsin Ave. $40 to $50 per date, on sale 10 a.m. Saturday at the box office, (414) 342-7283 and therave.com . 
Thomas Rhett: 8 p.m. Dec. 12, the Rave. $28.50 to $36.50. 
Noel Torres: 8 p.m. Nov. 21, the Rave. $31.50 to $66.50. 
Nate Ruess: 8 p.m. Oct. 16, Tarble Arena, Carthage College, 2001 Alford Park Dr., Kenosha. $15 for full-time students, $25 for general public at carthage.edu . 
Jason Isbell: 8 p.m. Feb. 23, Pabst Theater, 144 E. Wells St. $35.50, on sale noon Friday at the box office, the Riverside Theater box office (116 W. Wisconsin Ave.), (414) 286-3663 and pabsttheater.org . 
The Musical Box performs Genesis' 'The Black Show': 8 p.m. Feb. 4, Pabst Theater. $39.50 to $85, on sale noon Friday. 
Henry Rollins: 8 p.m. Feb. 14, Turner Hall Ballroom, 1040 N. 4th St. $27.50, on sale noon Friday. 
Marc Roberge of O.A.R. (acoustic): 8 p.m. Dec. 18, Turner Hall Ballroom. $29.50, on sale noon Friday. 
JoJo: 8 p.m. Nov. 16, Turner Hall Ballroom. $22.25 in advance, $25 day of show, on sale 10 a.m. Friday. 
BoDeans: 8 p.m. Nov. 19 and 20, Northern Lights Theater, Potawatomi Hotel & Casino, 1721 W. Canal St. $39 to $49, on sale noon Monday at the box office and through Ticketmaster. 
Whitford/St. Holmes: 8 p.m. Nov. 12, Northern Lights Theater, Potawatomi Hotel & Casino. $25 to $35. 
Jeff Tracta: 8 p.m. Nov. 13, Northern Lights Theater, Potawatomi Hotel & Casino. $25 to $35. 
Colt Ford: 8:30 p.m. Nov. 7, Route 20 Outhouse, 14001 Washington Ave., Sturtevant. $25 at the box office, (262) 898-7900 and route20outhouse.com . 
Tab Benoit: 8:30 p.m. Dec. 18, Route 20 Outhouse. $20 to $45. 
Tortoise: 9 p.m. Jan. 24, Mad Planet, 533 E. Center St. $12 in advance through mad-planet.net ; $15 day of show. 
Murphy Beds: 7:30 p.m. Oct. 17, Irish Cultural and Heritage Center, 2133 W. Wisconsin Ave. $15 for students, $21 in advance, $25 day of show, available at ichc.net. 
Steve Forbert: 8 p.m. Jan. 22, Shank Hall, 1434 N. Farwell Ave. $20 at the box office, (866) 468-3401 or ticketweb.com. 
Think Floyd USA: 8 p.m. Jan. 23, Shank Hall. Price to be determined. 
Protohype and Herobust: 9 p.m. Nov. 28, Miramar Theatre, 2844 N. Oakland Ave. $20 to $60 at the box office and ticketfly.com. 
Hurt Everybody: 8 p.m. Oct. 22, Miramar Theatre. $15. 
Mushroomhead: 8 p.m. Oct. 28, the Metal Grill, 5036 S. Packard Ave., Cudahy. $15 at the box office and themetalgrill.com . 
Texas in July: 5 p.m. Dec. 6, the Metal Grill. $12. 
Soil: 7 p.m. Dec. 10, the Metal Grill. $15. 
Gomorrah and Wulf: 8 p.m. Oct. 16, Frank's Power Plant, 2800 S. Kinnickinnic Ave. $6. 
Bantam Foxes: 9 p.m. Oct. 17, Frank's Power Plant. $5. 
Beast in the Field and Caustic Casanova: 7:30 p.m. Oct. 19, Frank's Power Plant. $5. 
Death and Memphis: 9 p.m. Oct. 24, Frank's Power Plant. $5. 
Daphne Lee Martin: 8 p.m. Oct. 25, Frank's Power Plant. $5. 
Those Manic Seas: 9 p.m. Oct. 29, Frank's Power Plant. $5. NEWS & NOTES 
■The Oct. 17 acoustic concert with Jana Kramer, Kelsea Ballerini, Ashley Monroe and Mickey Guyton at Red Rock Saloon is sold out. 
■ Melanie Martinez's Oct. 21 concert at Turner Hall Ballroom is sold out.
